Package: latter
Type: Package
Title: Train, use and evaluate Self-Supervised models on a given dataset.
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "David", "de la Rosa",
      email = "drrosa@ujaen.es",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: A set of tools to train and evaluate Self-Supervised Learning 
    models into a given dataset. You provide the data and create and train a model using 
    'fit_extractor'. Then, you can use the pretrained model, stored in your machine,
    to extract the latent representations of a given dataset using 
    'extract_features'. The package allows the evaluation of the 
    representations by training a classifier with 
    'train_classifier_on_extracted_features', and testing it with 'downstream_prediction'.
    To facilitate the use of latter, we have implemented a 'recipes' new step to train
    a model and extract the latent representation of a given dataset.
